verses.text_plain: And there went a man of the house of Levi, and took to wife a daughter of Levi.
verses.verse_html: 1And there went a man of the house of Levi, and took to wife a daughter of Levi.

verses.text_plain: And the woman conceived, and bare a son: and when she saw him that he was a goodly child, she hid him three months.
verses.verse_html: 2And the woman conceived, and bare a son: and when she saw him that he was a goodly child, she hid him three months.

verses.text_plain: And when she could not longer hide him, she took for him an ark of bulrushes, and daubed it with slime and with pitch, and put the child therein; and she laid it in the flags by the river’s brink.
verses.verse_html: 3And when she could not longer hide him, she took for him an ark of bulrushes, and daubed it with slime and with pitch, and put the child therein; and she laid it in the flags by the river’s brink.

verses.text_plain: And his sister stood afar off, to wit what would be done to him.
verses.verse_html: 4And his sister stood afar off, to wit what would be done to him.

verses.text_plain: And the daughter of Pharaoh came down to wash herself at the river; and her maidens walked along by the river’s side; and when she saw the ark among the flags, she sent her maid to fetch it.
verses.verse_html: 5And the daughter of Pharaoh came down to wash herself at the river; and her maidens walked along by the river’s side; and when she saw the ark among the flags, she sent her maid to fetch it.

verses.text_plain: And when she had opened it, she saw the child: and, behold, the babe wept. And she had compassion on him, and said, This is one of the Hebrews’ children.
verses.verse_html: 6And when she had opened it, she saw the child: and, behold, the babe wept. And she had compassion on him, and said, This is one of the Hebrews’ children.

verses.text_plain: Then said his sister to Pharaoh’s daughter, Shall I go and call to thee a nurse of the Hebrew women, that she may nurse the child for thee?
verses.verse_html: 7Then said his sister to Pharaoh’s daughter, Shall I go and call to thee a nurse of the Hebrew women, that she may nurse the child for thee?

verses.text_plain: And Pharaoh’s daughter said to her, Go. And the maid went and called the child’s mother.
verses.verse_html: 8And Pharaoh’s daughter said to her, Go. And the maid went and called the child’s mother.

verses.text_plain: And Pharaoh’s daughter said unto her, Take this child away, and nurse it for me, and I will give thee thy wages. And the woman took the child, and nursed it.
verses.verse_html: 9And Pharaoh’s daughter said unto her, Take this child away, and nurse it for me, and I will give thee thy wages. And the woman took the child, and nursed it.

tokens.text: it for me, and I will give

verses.text_plain: And the child grew, and she brought him unto Pharaoh’s daughter, and he became her son. And she called his name Moses: and she said, Because I drew him out of the water.
verses.verse_html:
10And the child grew, and she brought him unto Pharaoh’s daughter, and he became her son. And she called his name Moses: and she said, Because I drew him out of the water. ▼
▼ Moses: that is, Drawn out

footnotes.body_html: ▼ Moses: that is, Drawn out

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass in those days, when Moses was grown, that he went out unto his brethren, and looked on their burdens: and he spied an Egyptian smiting an Hebrew, one of his brethren.
verses.verse_html: 11And it came to pass in those days, when Moses was grown, that he went out unto his brethren, and looked on their burdens: and he spied an Egyptian smiting an Hebrew, one of his brethren.

tokens.text: And it came to pass in those days

verses.text_plain: And he looked this way and that way, and when he saw that there was no man, he slew the Egyptian, and hid him in the sand.
verses.verse_html: 12And he looked this way and that way, and when he saw that there was no man, he slew the Egyptian, and hid him in the sand.

verses.text_plain: And when he went out the second day, behold, two men of the Hebrews strove together: and he said to him that did the wrong, Wherefore smitest thou thy fellow?
verses.verse_html: 13And when he went out the second day, behold, two men of the Hebrews strove together: and he said to him that did the wrong, Wherefore smitest thou thy fellow?

tokens.text: to him that did the wrong

verses.text_plain: And he said, Who made thee a prince and a judge over us? intendest thou to kill me, as thou killedst the Egyptian? And Moses feared, and said, Surely this thing is known.
verses.verse_html:
14And he said, Who made thee a prince and a judge over us? intendest thou to kill me, as thou killedst the Egyptian? And Moses feared, and said, Surely this thing is known. ▼
▼ a prince: Heb. a man, a prince

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a prince: Heb. a man, a prince
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a prince: Heb. a man, a prince

verses.text_plain: Now when Pharaoh heard this thing, he sought to slay Moses. But Moses fled from the face of Pharaoh, and dwelt in the land of Midian: and he sat down by a well.
verses.verse_html: 15Now when Pharaoh heard this thing, he sought to slay Moses. But Moses fled from the face of Pharaoh, and dwelt in the land of Midian: and he sat down by a well.

verses.text_plain: Now the priest of Midian had seven daughters: and they came and drew water, and filled the troughs to water their father’s flock.
verses.verse_html:
16Now the priest of Midian had seven daughters: and they came and drew water, and filled the troughs to water their father’s flock. ▼
▼ priest: or, prince

verses.text_plain: And the shepherds came and drove them away: but Moses stood up and helped them, and watered their flock.
verses.verse_html: 17And the shepherds came and drove them away: but Moses stood up and helped them, and watered their flock.

verses.text_plain: And when they came to Reuel their father, he said, How is it that ye are come so soon to day?
verses.verse_html:
18And when they came to Reuel their father, he said, How is it that ye are come so soon to day? ▼
▼ Reuel: called also Jethro, or, Jether

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Reuel: called also Jethro, or, Jether
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Reuel: called also Jethro, or, Jether

verses.text_plain: And they said, An Egyptian delivered us out of the hand of the shepherds, and also drew water enough for us, and watered the flock.
verses.verse_html: 19And they said, An Egyptian delivered us out of the hand of the shepherds, and also drew water enough for us, and watered the flock.

verses.text_plain: And he said unto his daughters, And where is he? why is it that ye have left the man? call him, that he may eat bread.
verses.verse_html: 20And he said unto his daughters, And where is he? why is it that ye have left the man? call him, that he may eat bread.

verses.text_plain: And Moses was content to dwell with the man: and he gave Moses Zipporah his daughter.
verses.verse_html: 21And Moses was content to dwell with the man: and he gave Moses Zipporah his daughter.

verses.text_plain: And she bare him a son, and he called his name Gershom: for he said, I have been a stranger in a strange land.
verses.verse_html:
22And she bare him a son, and he called his name Gershom: for he said, I have been a stranger in a strange land. ▼
▼ Gershom: that is, A stranger here

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Gershom: that is, A stranger here
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Gershom: that is, A stranger here

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass in process of time, that the king of Egypt died: and the children of Israel sighed by reason of the bondage, and they cried, and their cry came up unto God by reason of the bondage.
verses.verse_html: 23And it came to pass in process of time, that the king of Egypt died: and the children of Israel sighed by reason of the bondage, and they cried, and their cry came up unto God by reason of the bondage.

tokens.text: And it came to pass in process

verses.text_plain: And God heard their groaning, and God remembered his covenant with Abraham, with Isaac, and with Jacob.
verses.verse_html: 24And God heard their groaning, and God remembered his covenant with Abraham, with Isaac, and with Jacob.

verses.text_plain: And God looked upon the children of Israel, and God had respect unto them.
verses.verse_html:
25And God looked upon the children of Israel, and God had respect unto them. ▼
▼ had…: Heb. knew
